        [
          "Staff Generated History"
        ],
        [
          "You grew up in Lynwood in the gangs.  Your entire family was in the gangs and it was the only life you knew. You were rather good at the life, you worked your way up and by the time you were 25, you had only been to juvie twice, and county once.  You had respect from your affiliates, you ran dealers, had several pimps paying you for protection, and were leading the good life.  Then a rather nasty gunfight erupted down the street from your place, you went outside with your AK to wast some fuckers stupid enough to shoot up you neighborhood and met this beautiful woman on your lawn, she was covered in burned clothes and looked pretty messed up.  She was bending over this guy and seemed to be making out with him, but the dude was out.  Then she looked up and captured your eyes.  Next thing you knew this chick was living in your basement and you loved working for her, she was some strange blood sucking vampire chick, but damn she was hot.  You loved being around her and doing stuff for her.  She was fighting the Asians (they were the fuckers that dared attack her) and she needed help doing so, you had contacts and skill, and she let you help her in all the little ways you could.  2014 was the best year of your life.  Then in February of 2015, she embraced you as you had proven yourself invaluable to her.  She told you of the war going on in LA and the sides involved, and how you were very much not what her clan normally wanted, but in LA you were what they needed.  Your \"art\" was survival and revenge, a much better way to live in LA than sculpting and poetry.  The Anarchs sound like the people you have worked among all your life, the Sabbat sound like some crazy violent nasties, and the Camarilla seem to be the white collar that you have been locked out of by birth.  Theresa was caught and killed by the Asians last month, and that really pissed you off, you figure the only ones taking the fight to the Asians right now is the Camarilla and you should go check them out."
        ],
        [
